  {
    "text": "mm It\ncan be modiﬁed via the conﬁguration option string of the MV A method to be boosted fsee Option\nTables qp and qq on pages pou and pou for boosted decision treesk and Option Table qs for general\nclassiﬁer boosting xmpg if one wants to use an unweighted average of the boosted decision trees or\nclassiﬁers instead of the weighted onem\nFor regression trees k the AdaBoost algorithm needs to be modiﬁedm TMV A uses here the solcalled",
    "metadata": {
      "source": "data\\Multivariate analysis.pdf",
      "chunk_index": 157
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "nem\nFor regression trees k the AdaBoost algorithm needs to be modiﬁedm TMV A uses here the solcalled\nAdaBoostmRq algorithm [ qv]m The idea is similar to AdaBoost albeit with a redeﬁned loss per event\nto account for the the deviation of the estimated target value from the true onem Moreoverk as there\nare no longer correctly and wrongly classiﬁed eventsk all events need to be reweighted depending on\ntheir individual loss k which – for event k – is given by\nLinear y Lfkg=\n|y(k)− ˆy(k)|\nmax",
    "metadata": {
      "source": "data\\Multivariate analysis.pdf",
      "chunk_index": 158
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "ending on\ntheir individual loss k which – for event k – is given by\nLinear y Lfkg=\n|y(k)− ˆy(k)|\nmax\nevents k￿\n(|y(k￿\n)− ˆy(k￿\n|)\n, fqtg\nSquare y Lfkg=\n￿\n|y(k)− ˆy(k)|\nmax\nevents k￿\n(|y(k￿\n)− ˆy(k￿\n|)\n￿2\n, fqug\nExponential y Lfkg=p − exp\n￿\n−\n|y(k)− ˆy(k)|\nmax\nevents k￿\n(|y(k￿\n)− ˆy(k￿\n|)\n￿\n. fqvg\nThe average loss of the classiﬁer y(i)\nover the whole training samplek ￿L￿\n(i)\n=\n￿\nevents k￿ wfk￿\ngL(i)\nfk￿\ngk",
    "metadata": {
      "source": "data\\Multivariate analysis.pdf",
      "chunk_index": 159
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "e loss of the classiﬁer y(i)\nover the whole training samplek ￿L￿\n(i)\n=\n￿\nevents k￿ wfk￿\ngL(i)\nfk￿\ngk\ncan be considered to be the analogon to the error fraction in classiﬁcationm Given ￿L￿k one computes\nthe quantity β(i) = ￿L￿\n(i)\n/fp −￿ L￿\n(i)\ngk which is used in the boosting of the eventsk and for the\ncombination of the regression methods belonging to the boosted collectionm The boosting weightk\nw(i+1)\nfkgk for event k and boost step ii p thus reads\nw\n(i+1)\nfkg= w\n(i)\nfkg·β\n1− L(i)\n(k)\n(i)",
