  },
  {
    "text": "d leaf. This minimization is closely related\nto minimizing the binomial log-likelihood[4]. It can be\nshown that E(e−yF(x))i sm i n i m i z e da t\nF(x)=\n1\n2\nln\nP(y=1|x)\nP(y=−1|x)\n=\n1\n2\nln\np(x)\n1−p(x)\nLety∗=(y+1 )/2. It is then easy to show that\ne−yF(x)\n=\n|y∗−p(x)|\n√\np(x)(1−p(x))\nThe right-hand side is known as the χstatistic. χ2is\naq u a d r a t i v ea p p r o x i m a t i o nt ot h el o g - l i k e l i h o o d ,s o χ\ncan be considered a gentler alternative. It turns out",
